🔷 Common Security Threats

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1️⃣ SQL Injection

👉 Injecting malicious queries

❌ Unsafe:

```javascript
const query = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = '" + email + "'";
```

✔ Safe:

```javascript
// Use parameterized queries / ORM (Mongoose)
User.findOne({ email });
```

---

2️⃣ Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)

👉 Injecting malicious scripts into frontend

✔ Solution:

* Escape user input
* Use proper templating

---

3️⃣ Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)

👉 Unauthorized actions from authenticated users

✔ Solution:

* Use CSRF tokens

---

4️⃣ Brute Force Attacks

👉 Trying many passwords

✔ Solution:

* Rate limiting
* Strong passwords

