🔷 Password Security (Very Important ⭐)

Never store plain passwords ❌

---

Use bcrypt

```bash
npm install bcrypt
```

---

Hash Password

```javascript
const bcrypt = require("bcrypt");

const hashed = await bcrypt.hash("password123", 10);
```

---

Compare Password

```javascript
const match = await bcrypt.compare("password123", hashed);
```

---

🔷 Secure Authentication

✔ Use JWT or sessions
✔ Set token expiry
✔ Use secure cookies

---

🔷 Environment Variables

Store secrets in `.env`:

```text
PORT=3000
JWT_SECRET=mysecretkey
```

Use:

```javascript
require("dotenv").config();
```

---

🔷 Use Helmet (Security Middleware)

```bash
npm install helmet
```

```javascript
const helmet = require("helmet");
app.use(helmet());
```

✔ Secures HTTP headers

---

🔷 Enable CORS Safely

```bash
npm install cors
```

```javascript
const cors = require("cors");

app.use(cors({
  origin: "http://localhost:3000"
}));
```

✔ Restrict access

---

🔷 Rate Limiting

```bash
npm install express-rate-limit
```

```javascript
const rateLimit = require("express-rate-limit");

const limiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000,
  max: 100
});

app.use(limiter);
```

✔ Prevent abuse

---

🔷 Input Validation

```bash
npm install express-validator
```

```javascript
const { body } = require("express-validator");

app.post("/user",
  body("email").isEmail(),
  (req, res) => {
    res.send("Valid data");
  }
);
```

---

🔷 Secure Cookies

```javascript
res.cookie("token", "abc123", {
  httpOnly: true,
  secure: true
});
```

---

🔷 HTTPS (Very Important ⭐)

✔ Always use HTTPS

```text
http:// ❌  
https:// ✔
```

---

